   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER SIXTY-TWO BEING CRUCIFIED WITH CHRIST</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND BEARING THE CROSS THE LORD'S DAY MORNING MESSAGE 3</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Date:The Lord's Day, April 25, 1948</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Place:Hardoon Road, Shanghai</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Speaker:Chen Keh-san, Witness Lee</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Scripture Reading: Isa 14:12-14; Gen 3:4-5; John 12:31; Col 2:14; Heb 2:14; John 19:30; Matt 27:50; 1 Sam 16:13; 2 Sam 2:4; 5:3</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Prayer: Lord, may none of us here miss Your presence.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>In particular, may those who desire to rise up but who cannot rise up not miss Your presence.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Lord, if You want to receive a better worship from us, we ask that You do a deeper work within us.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Do not let any one of us slip by.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Do not let anyone come and go empty-handed.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Do not let anyone come and go in sorrow.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>CHRIST DESTROYING THE FALLEN SATAN</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>THROUGH THE CROSS</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Brother Chen Keh-san: Isaiah 14 and Genesis 3 show us where sin came from.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>In Isaiah 14, Satan said five times, "I will."</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Satan is a creature, and God is the Creator.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The creature cannot demand anything from the Creator.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>A carpenter is the maker, and a chair is being made by the carpenter.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The chair cannot demand anything from the carpenter.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>If you pay attention to the word of the serpent in Genesis 3, you will notice that his words are the same in nature as the words in Isaiah 14.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>This nature has come into man's heart today.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Everyone is under Satan's hand.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The Lord came, and Satan's place is lost.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The Lord accomplished redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>He is the "foreign" One, the real Foreigner.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>He was uplifted, and Satan was defeated.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>THE DEATH OF CHRIST TERMINATING THE FLESH</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Today, Satan utilizes man's flesh and makes it his puppet.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>However, man's flesh is what Christ put on.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>When Christ died, we were all hung on the cross, and the flesh was terminated Gal 5:24 .</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>In this way, Satan became naked.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Hebrews 2 says that Christ through death destroyed Satan who has the might of death.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>This is like the Japanese Emperor Hirohito being condemned.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>When he was condemned, the whole Japanese nation was condemned.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>It is a small thing for one man to be condemned, but it is a great thing for a whole nation to be condemned.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>The Bible says that the whole world was judged when One was lifted up John 12:31 .</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>The Lord accomplished a great thing on the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>His death terminated the flesh.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>THE CROSS BEING THE GROUND OF OUR VICTORY</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>The cross is the place of death.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>It is also the place of victory.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>Other than the cross, there is no victory.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>To Satan, the cross is the place of condemnation.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>To us, it is the place of victory.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>For this reason, no Christian can leave the ground of the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>If they leave, they will be defeated.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>Some Fukienese say constantly, "Satan is defeated," as if they are chanting curses.</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>Such chanting will never defeat Satan.</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>Only the cross can defeat Satan.</S>
   </TEXT>
